{"id": "EUVD-2025-27890", "enisaUuid": "5b6838de-08f6-3313-a442-bb8641261a3c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: airoha: fix potential use-after-free in airoha_npu_get()\n\nnp->name was being used after calling of_node_put(np), which\nreleases the node and can lead to a use-after-free bug.\nPreviously, of_node_put(np) was called unconditionally after\nof_find_device_by_node(np), which could result in a use-after-free if\npdev is NULL.\n\nThis patch moves of_node_put(np) after the error check to ensure\nthe node is only released after both the error and success cases\nare handled appropriately, preventing potential resource issues.", "datePublished": "2025-08-16T12:30:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T18:32:48", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/df6bf96b41e547e350667bc4c143be53646d070d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3cd582e7d0787506990ef0180405eb6224fa90a6", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38536"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38536"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "31d06ac8-7db0-392a-8a4b-d158be1bc8a9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "23290c7bc190def4e1ca61610992d9b7c32e33f3 <3cd582e7d0787506990ef0180405eb6224fa90a6"}, {"id": "47eed5c0-2c8b-36da-99c3-f9ceca4c1853", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.8"}, {"id": "56ec2fbe-18f6-321e-94e4-9e47ae8e2eff", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "893372b6-b28d-30e5-bdcf-8a185ca80bf3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.15"}, {"id": "a16d7c12-936c-32f7-95c7-ff1bdecf6c56", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "b424a2a7-fa44-3553-88a2-1854a4ec8db0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "23290c7bc190def4e1ca61610992d9b7c32e33f3 <df6bf96b41e547e350667bc4c143be53646d070d"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "7b7ffdf1-68ab-35b9-aa49-de84e651b8b9", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}]